race.description: Tab Venue Boost Country Boosted Handicap (Bm50)
race.comment: Tricky. COSMIC RIDE (2) led and was narrowly beaten at Canberra three back in a 60 and after a disappointing effort following, placed here in a CL3. Carries more weight at this level but is well-placed to go one better. TILLMAN (3) led and missed a nose here in a 58 over 1600m. Has a handy 3kg claim today and the early speed to navigate the tricky barrier. Has claims. AIRLINER (4) hasn't won for a long while but just missed at Nowra before finishing the race off well enough there after a slow start. Can't be ruled out. MEMPHIS TENNESSEE (6) peaks off a Wagga placing over a mile at this level. Coming back 140m shouldn't bother, and he's some hope at a big price with average luck from the awkward gate.
